==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: heated
<hw>heated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>characterized by great
warmth and intensity of feeling; <as>as, a <ex>heated</ex>
argument</as>. Opposite of <ant>dispassionate, passionless</ant>.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ardent, fervent, fervid, fiery, hot, impassioned,
perfervid, torrid.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>supplied with a mechanism for heating; -- of
structures or devices; <as>as, a <ex>heated</ex> fishing cabin</as>.
Opposite of <ant>unheated</ant>.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heater</ent>⟦br⟧
